Using Decision Tree Classifier with Indian liver patient data to predict healthy or unhealthy livers

Dataset used can be found at:

https://www.dropbox.com/s/3l3sf22ex49dr79/ilpd.csv?dl=1

As the Gender attribute uses categorical data, rather than numerical data, this is remedied by One-Hot Encoding to change the Gender attribute into two binary attributes.

In [6]:
df = pd.get_dummies(df, columns=["Gender"]) #One Hot Encoding Gender column
df.head(5) #Looking at new dataframe to observe new columns

Training and generating the Decision Tree Classifier model

The model was trained using a training set split comprised of 20% of the overall dataset.

In [7]:
x = df.drop(['Label'], axis=1) #removing the classification from the test set
y = df.Label
print (y[0:5])

0    1
1    1
2    1
3    1
4    1
Name: Label, dtype: int64
In [11]:
x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x,y, test_size=0.8, random_state=2) #using sklearn to create the training data and test data split.
print ("Training Set Size: ",x_train.shape)

Training Set Size:  (113, 11)
In [12]:
clf = DecisionTreeClassifier() #initialising the decision tree classifier

clf = clf.fit(x_train, y_train) #feeding the training set into the classifier

y_pred = clf.predict(x_test) #predicting the classifiers of the test set
In [13]:
print("Accuracy: ",metrics.accuracy_score(y_test,y_pred)) #Outputting the accuracy value of the classifier by comparing to the actual classification

Accuracy:  0.6710816777041942

Visualising the Decision Tree Model

In [25]:
from sklearn.tree import export_graphviz
from six import StringIO
from IPython.display import Image
import pydotplus

feature_cols = ['Age','Total_Bilirubin','Direct_Bilirubin','Total_Proteins','Albumin','AG_Ratio','SGPT','SGOT','Alkphos','Gender_Female','Gender_Male']
dot_data = StringIO()
export_graphviz(clf, out_file=dot_data,
                filled =True, rounded =True,
                special_characters =True,
                feature_names = feature_cols,
                class_names=['0','1'])
graph = pydotplus.graph_from_dot_data(dot_data.getvalue())
graph.write_png('decisiontree.png')
Image(graph.create_png())
